23/06/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Economy Minister Ali Babacan and IMF Mission Desk Chief Riza Moghadam held a joint press conference Tuesday (22 June), marking the end of the mission's talks with local authorities. 
Babacan said an agreement was reached on the steps that Turkey must take before approval of the 8th programme review, as well as on the content of the supplementary Letter of Intent that Turkish authorities must submit to the Fund.
In other news, Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan announced on Tuesday that parliament would recess on 15 July, rather than 1 July. 
The additional two weeks will be used to finalise work crucial to the European Commission report on Turkey. 
(Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 22/06/04)
